    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nWith GIT_DIR+GIT_WORK_TREE set in the environment, the hover on git commits in the vim.pack.update() confirmation buffer is broken:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1209\" height=\"467\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6861555a-4f13-427b-b05b-537d057626e2\" />\r\n\r\nThe current tests do not test for this LSP functionality with GIT_DIR/GIT_WORK_TREE.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nTemporarily remove GIT_DIR/GIT_WORK_TREE from the environment for the system call to git. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"1053\" height=\"505\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eb148e7a-7680-453d-9864-9800d8de7507\" />\r\n\r\nMost other git calls that the in-process lsp makes already do this indirectly, but hover calls vim.system() directly.\r\n\r\n\r\nI only added a test for the textDocument/hover functionality because it's what is fixed in this PR and I wasn't sure how  to accomodate tests for all of the in-process lsp's features without restructuring the tests or making them very redundant.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-22T08:46:48Z",
